<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-2907] durable_writes flag cannot be changed via the CLI (system does not process KsDef.durable_writes option properly).</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-2907</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I am unable to change the durable_writes option in the CLI. Here are the commands to replicate the problem on a clean install:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;create keyspace test;&lt;br/&gt;
update keyspace test with durable_writes=false;&lt;br/&gt;
show keyspaces;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It will still say:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Keyspace: test:&lt;br/&gt;
  Replication Strategy: org.apache.cassandra.locator.NetworkTopologyStrategy&lt;br/&gt;
  Durable Writes: true&lt;br/&gt;
    Options: &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;datacenter1:1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
  Column Families:&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;PS: I looked in the tests of the CLI code of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-2683&quot; title=&quot;Allow writes to bypass the commit log for certain keyspaces&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-2683&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-2683&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; and saw that the feature actually is not properly tested: the flag is set, but never tested.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
